d) Experience with community engagement and coordination with a wide range of stakeholders

Job Summary:
Come join PPCRM and harness the opportunity to become a part of Canadian history and partake in a challenging cooperative work term that is intellectually stimulating, promoting personal and professional growth within the Science and Parliamentary Infrastructure Branch's dynamic workplace environment.

Background

Within the Science and Parliamentary Infrastructure Branch, the Program, Portfolio and Client Relationship Management (PPCRM) sector assumes the role of a steward and corporate owner of the Parliamentary Precinct to preserve and maintain the integrity of the real property portfolio.
 
Students will be working on high level long term strategic planning documents regarding Parliament hill and its surrounding buildings. The documents will be used in investment and decision making regarding Parliament Hill's rehabilitation plans and will be presented to high level managers.
 
Planning documents includes a review and analysis of the following:

Heritage consideration documents;
Building Condition Reports;
Environmental sustainability and greening reports;
Physical and virtual security plans;
Legal documents;
Accessibility reports;
High level documents prepared by specialists such as engineers, architects, accounts etc.


Our Mission

To provide strategic direction and oversight to ensure sound stewardship of real property assets in order to enable the delivery of mandated programs within approved policies and standards, recommending the allocation of funding for the delivery of short- to mid-term programs in such a manner as to achieve the long-term portfolio plan.
 
Moreover, the Owner-Investor Directorate provides vision and direction in the following areas:

Strategic Planning;
Portfolio Management;
Portfolio Programming; and
Investment Management and Program Governance.

Job Responsibilities:
The Junior Investment Analyst will support Owner-Investor at full capacity, with the following responsibilities:

Support Owner-Investor by gathering required data and information;
Help prepare high level documents by researching, analyzing, preparing and verifying data used to develop reports and other documents;
Review current information, reports and documents such as Statement of Requirements, Investment Analysis Reports, Owner-Investor Tracker, Investment Decisions Tracker;
Develop and maintain information sources;
Complete Financial Analysis;
Participate, monitor and develop financial tracking tools as well as performance indicators; and
Participate in tours of Parliament Hill and surrounding building.

Required Skills:
Essential Requirements:

Excellent verbal and written communication skills;
Strong analytical skills;
Interpersonal skills and works well in a team environment;
Self-starter, ability to work under minimal supervision;
Well organized, resourceful and demonstrates initiative;
Manages priorities and ability to comply with established timelines;
Experienced in Microsoft Office applications such as Excel, Word, PowerPoint, Outlook;
Proficient knowledge of English and French; and
Ability to obtain Secret security clearance.


Asset:

Knowledge and recognition of Canadian heritage considerations and their impact on government projects;
In depth knowledge of finance including discounted cash flow analysis and cost-benefit analysis;
Proficient in Excel, notably the ability to create and manipulate pivot tables, data and create charts;
Working knowledge of SIGMA; and
Working knowledge of GC docs.

